OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FArchie Battersbee's family 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fgranted more time to appeal
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fagainst ruling             
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The parents of a boy at the centre of a
OL,6, life support treatment fight have been 
OL,7, given more time to make an appeal.     
OL,9,FArchie Battersbee,12, was found        
OL,10,Funconscious at home in Southend, Essex,
OL,11,Fon 7 April.                            
OL,13,FOn Monday his family lost a request to 
OL,14,Fappeal a High Court ruling that stated 
OL,15,Ftreatment could lawfully end.          
OL,17,FThe Christian Legal Centre, who support
OL,18,Fthe family, said they have been given  
OL,19,Fan extra day to make an application to 
OL,20,Fthe European Court of Human Rights.    
